The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, July 30, 2004  Timeout
				 																DRAMA				 																																	 July 31 at Academy of Fine Arts; 3 pm: Natyaanan presents Continuity. Dir: Chandan Sen.				 																																	 July 31 at Madhusudan Mancha, 6 pm; August 1 at Girish Mancha, 3 pm amp; 6 pm: Natyaranga presents Siraj-ud Daulah, with Santu Mukherjee, Surajit Banerjee, Goutam Mukherjee, Shyamal Chakraborty and Nandita Roy Chowdhury comprising the cast. Direction: Swapan Sengupta.				 																																	 July 31 at Girish Mancha; 6.30 pm: Bohurupee presents its latest production, Nishiddha Thikana. Director: Debesh Roychowdhury.				 																																	 August 1 at Academy of Fine Arts; 10.30 am: Ganakrishti presents its latest play, Satoreoi July. Direction: Bratya Basu.				 																																	 August 1 at Academy of Fine Arts; 3 pm: Swapnasandhani presents Buddhadev Boses Kolkatar Elektra. Direction and acting: Koushik Sen.				 																																	 August 1 at Purbasree Mancha, Bharatiyam; 6 pm: Kolkata Eso Natak Shikhi, a drama group of young enthusiasts aged five to 15, will stage three one-act plays: Maranastra (The Lethal Weapon), Dukhuramer Arupkatha (The Tale of Dukhuram) and Ekta Mather Janya (For a Playground).				 																 Art				 																																	 July 30 at the Tea Lounge, Oberoi Grand; 7.30 pm: The Oberoi Grand and Spandan Art Gallery presents an Art Walk, A Tryst with Nature  an exhibition of paintings by Rana Roy, Ambarish Brahmachari, Partha Bhattacharya, Moloy Chandan Saha, Abhijit Dutta, Sanatan Dinda, Sheila Kapoor, Kanchanmala Ghosh and Samir Paul. A part of the proceeds collected will go towards charity.				 																																	 Till July 31 at Chemould Art Gallery, Park Street; 10 am - 6 pm: Samantoral, in association with Ratrilekha Communication, presents an exhibition of paintings and sculptures by well-known artists.				 																																	 Till July 31 at Idiyas Gallery, 15 Dover Road; 10.30 am - 7.30 pm: An exhibition of paintings and sculptures by a group of talented artists.				 																																	 Till August 7 (except Sunday) at Galerie 88, 28B Shakespeare Sarani; 3 pm - 7 pm: Galerie 88 hosts the Parthasarathi Retrospective.				 																																	 Till July 30 at Chitrakoot Art Gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: An exhibition of paintings by Arun Goswami and Avisankar Mitra.				 																																	 Till August 15 (except Mondays) at Akar Prakar, P-238 Hindustan Park; 11 am - 8 pm: A rare collection of early drawings and etchings of K Laxma Goud.				 																EXHIBITION				 																																	 Till August 10 at Uma, 2/4A Sarat Bose Road (near Minto Park): British Council is hosting Global Local, an exhibition of the works of Indian designers who have imbibed British design styles in their creations. The exhibition showcases the works of at least two city designers, Sabyasachi Mukherjee and Darshan Shah, among others such as Anshu Arora Sen, George Chakravarthi, Manish Arora, Maithili Ahluwalia and Abraham Thakore.				 																POETRY				 																																	 July 30 at Srijan rooftop; 5 pm: Srijan hosts Youth Poetry Festival with the presence of and comments by poets Nawal, Shahnaz Nabi and Srijato, and those responsible for publishing poetry, Badal Basu and Chitralekha Basu. Anchor: Shiladitya Roy.				 																HEALTH				 																																	 July 30 at Trimurti Apartment, 97 Park Street, 5th floor; 3 pm: The Boy Care presents The Body Care Cancer Awareness and Cancer Detection Workshop with specialist cancer doctors.				 																PHOTOGRAPHS				 																																	 Till July 31 at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 36C S.P. Mukherjee Road; 2 pm - 7.30 pm: Tamasha: Present Perfect  an exhibition of photographs by Sandesh Bhandare.				 																																	 Till July 30 at Gaganendra Pradarshasala; 2 pm - 8 pm: An exhibition of photographs taken by Bibek Guha.				 																TALK				 																																	 July 30 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Vivekananda Hall; 6.15 pm: Swami Prabhananda will speak in Bengali on Amukhya Gita.				 																																	 July 30 at Ramakrishna Vedanta Math, 19A amp; B Raja Rajkrishna Street; 7 pm: Dr Sasanka Bhusan Bandyopadhyay will speak on Brihadaranyaka Upanishad.				 																WORKSHOP				 																																	 August 1 onwards at 6 National Library Avenue: The Creative Arts begins workshops on theatre by Ramanjit, on creative writing by Swati Lal, on advertising and communication by Arthur Cardozo, and on fine arts by Samit Dey. Details at 9830775677; 23213225				 																																	 August 3 - 8 at 1 Merlin Park (opp. Ballygunge Tram Depot); 7 am - 9.30 am amp; 6 pm - 8.30 pm: Art of Living organises a workshop (for those who are 21 and above) to prepare one to live a happy and healthy life and be able to cope with day-to-day stresses and develop self-confidence. Details at 9831023445 / 31034764.
